parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loss of Acceleration with Air Conditioner On
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of acceleration when the air conditioner is on can cause unexpected slowing or stalling, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a sudden loss of power or acceleration when the air conditioner is turned on
the vehicle stalls or hesitates when accelerating
the engine RPM drops or fluctuates when the air conditioner is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes when the ABS system is activated can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
the ABS system malfunctions or activates unnecessarily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear and failure of brakes can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The brakes wear out quickly
the brake pads or rotors need to be replaced frequently
the brakes grind or make noise when applied
the vehicle vibrates or pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag module can prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the airbag warning light blinks or flashes
the airbag system malfunction indicator is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gas tank seam can cause gasoline to leak, resulting in a strong smell of gas, potential fire hazards, and environmental damage.
symptoms: Strong smell of gasoline inside the vehicle
gasoline dripping or leaking from the gas tank
spotting on the driveway or garage floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, damage to the vehicle, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Wobbling or vibrating of the vehicle
sudden loss of tire pressure
uneven tire wear
tire blowout
and damage to the vehicle's body or wheels.
